text: Maxwell Alejandro Frost (born January 17, 1997) is an American activist and Democratic politician. He is the U.S. representative for Florida's 10th congressional district since 2023. Before, he was the national organizing director for March for Our Lives. Frost is the first person from Generation Z to be elected to Congress and the second born in the 1990s, after Madison Cawthorn. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:American political activists Category:United States representatives from Florida Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:African-American politicians
